One strength of JIRA is its extensibility through various plug-ins - especially for workflow extensions (conditions, validators, post-functions) however, there is a downside:

Especially when upgrading JIRA it is easy to miss the installation of those plug-ins, as the first time this becomes apparent is when a transition fails. Also problematic is the situation where the class and/or package name of an extension changes. While rigid change management can prevent such situations it would be comforting to have a quick sanity check within JIRA itself. (Of course one could also click through all steps in all workflows...)

I therefore propose an extension of the Integrity Checker to search for workflow extensions which cannot be loaded with the exact workflow step, where it is used.

